A '''stunt coordinator''', usually an experienced [[stunt performer]], is hired by a [[TV]], [[film]] or [[theatre]] director or [[production company]] for [[stunt casting]] that is to arrange the casting (stunt players and stunt doubles) and performance of [[stunt]]s for a film, television programme or a live audience.

Where the film requires a [[stunt]], and involves the use of [[stunt performer]]s, the Stunt Coordinator will arrange the casting and performance of the stunt, working closely with the Director.

In many cases, the stunt coordinator budgets, designs and choreographs the stunt sequence to suit the script and the director's vision.

There are two [[Primetime Emmy Award]]s for [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Stunt Coordination|Outstanding Stunt Coordination]]—one for Outstanding Stunt Coordination for a Drama Series, Miniseries or Movie and another for Outstanding Stunt Coordination for a Comedy Series or Variety Program.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Pond|first1=Steve|title=New Emmy Rules Say Yes to Funny Stunts, No to Supporting Actors|url=http://www.thewrap.com/awards/column-post/new-emmy-rules-say-yes-funny-stunts-no-supporting-actors-83961/|work=The Wrap|date=April 11, 2013}}</ref>

